WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
Motion in a straight line begins with position, displacement, and time.

00:04.000 --> 00:08.000
Distance is total path length, while displacement keeps direction in view.

00:08.000 --> 00:12.000
Velocity describes how displacement changes over time.

00:12.000 --> 00:16.000
Acceleration describes how velocity changes over time.

00:16.000 --> 00:20.000
Use graph slopes and areas to solve motion questions faster.
